# SCSS UI (Fantager)

Authoritative doc: `docs/ui-guidelines.md`. Layout catalog: section 3.1.

## File placement

| Content | File |
|---------|------|
| Design tokens only | `assets/styles/abstracts/_tokens.scss` |
| Cross-cutting layout, tables, copy helpers | `assets/styles/components/_layout.scss`, `_shared.scss` |
| Atoms (btn, form, alert) | `_buttons.scss`, `_forms.scss`, `_flash.scss`, `_links.scss` |
| Screen/feature UI | `_hero.scss`, `_marketplace.scss`, `_formation.scss`, … |
| New component | Extend existing file for that domain; register in `app.scss` via `@use` if new file |

Use `@layer components { }` in component files. Tailwind `@apply` is OK **inside SCSS**, not in Twig.

## Colors & surfaces

- **Never** hard-code hex/rgba in component SCSS
- Use `var(--color-…)`, `var(--overlay-…)`, `var(--shadow-…)`
- Status tints: `color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-success-bg) 30%, transparent)`

## Naming (BEM-inspired)

```
.block              .btn  .game-panel
.block--modifier    .btn--sm  .layout-stack--lg
.block__element     .game-panel__title  .hero-panel__desc
.block-variant      .btn-primary  .alert-error
```

- lowercase-with-dashes
- Do not style `#id` selectors
- Prefix JS hooks with `js-` (never style `js-*` in SCSS)

## New layout or component class workflow

1. Check `_layout.scss` and domain `_*.scss` for existing class
2. Add semantic class with responsive rules in SCSS
3. Document in `docs/ui-guidelines.md` §3.1 if it is a reusable layout primitive
4. Use class from Twig — no utility mirror in templates

## Transitions & focus

- Hovers: `var(--transition-fast)`
- Focus rings: preserve `:focus-visible`; use `var(--focus-ring-color)`

## Optional verification (user-requested only)

Do not run automatically. When the user asks:

```bash
bash scripts/check-ui-compliance.sh
npm run build
```
